==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gabel
<hw>Ga"bel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>gabelle</ets>,
LL. <ets>gabella</ets>, <ets>gabulum</ets>, <ets>gablum</ets>; of
uncertain origin. Cf.<er>Gavel</er> tribute.]</ety> <fld>(O. Eng.
Law)</fld> <def>A rent, service, tribute, custom, tax, impost, or duty;
an excise.</def> <rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He enables St. Peter to pay his <qex>gabel</qex> by the ministry
of a fish.</q> <rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gabeler</ent>⟦br⟧
